The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 8: Backed by the goverment 

 as well as the Reserve Bank?s efforts to rein in the price 

 spiral, the fiscal 2004-05 ended with the rate of inflation 

 lower at 5.05 per cent for the week ended March 26. The 

 wholesale price index inflation fell by 0.06 per cent from 

 the previous week?s level of 5.11 per cent due to cheaper 

 edible oils and non-food products. However, food products, 

 including vegetables, were costlier during the period under 

 review. The point-to-point inflation was at 4.64 per cent 

 a year ago.

 New Delhi, April 8: The Union cabinet today approved the reclassification of Nagpur airport as an international one, with customs facilities. The cabinet agreed to reclassify the airport on a plea made by Maharashtra government, which sought the development of a world class multi-modal international passenger and cargo hub airport at Nagpur.

 New Delhi, April 8: Hindustan Motors, the C. K. Birla group flagship, today raised the price of its ambassador models between Rs 8000 and Rs 18,000. It has also implemented Bharat stage III emission norms across all categories.

 New Delhi, April 8: The Planning Commission has approved Power Finance Corp?s plans to raise capital through an IPO this fiscal in which the government is likely to offload up to 10 per cent stake.




